result.execSummary:
The defendant Kemar N Morgan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resist/Obstruct - County Ordinance. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Cash bail applied to fine. Sentence credit of 2 days to be applied in lieu of payment of balance of fine.

records.addlTxt: End of representation letter, dated 02/05/2020, filed by Atty. Menden.

Defendant Kemar N Morgan in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.  Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State makes a motion to amend to a County Ordinance Obstructing ticket, 13-103(c)(7).  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to the amended ordinance citation.  Court finds the defendant guilty.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Court sentences the defendant as follows:
Count 1:
FINE:  $267.50
Apply cash bail in the amount of $200.00.
Balance is $67.50.
Defendant has (2) days credit so court applies toward the balance and no money is due.
Plea/sentencing hearing on February 19, 2018 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Kemar N Morgan in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Menden requests an adjournment so the defendant can complete his community service.  Court grants.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for February 19, 2018 at 09:30 am.
